# ============================================
# Secrets & credentials
# ============================================
.env
vault/.env

# ============================================
# Vault — v3.5 flat per-agent layout
#
# Every agent (Main + custom) lives directly under the vault root as
# `vault/<id>/` with a hub file `agent-<id>.md`, a `CLAUDE.md`, and the
# six per-agent subfolders (Skills/, Routines/, Journal/, Reactions/,
# Lessons/, Notes/) plus `.workspace/` for pipeline runtime data.
#
# Commit policy:
#   - Shared root files (README.md, CLAUDE.md, Tooling.md) → committed
#   - `vault/main/` → committed (the "shipped default" Main agent that
#     every new user inherits from templates/main/ on first install)
#   - Custom agents (anything other than `main/`) → NOT committed
#     (personal content, per-machine)
#   - `.workspace/` and `.activity/` inside any agent → NEVER committed
#     (pure runtime data, sobrescrita a cada execução)
#   - `.graphs/` → NOT committed (generated daily by vault-graph-update)
#
# New users bootstrap by running:
#     python3 scripts/migrate_vault_per_agent.py
# which seeds `vault/main/` from `templates/main/`.
# ============================================

# Images are never committed (user-uploaded content, binary noise)
vault/Images/*
!vault/Images/.gitkeep

# One-shot migration backups produced by scripts/migrate_vault_per_agent.py
vault.backup-*/

# Knowledge graph (auto-generated daily by vault-graph-update routine)
vault/.graphs/
graphify-out/

# Obsidian user-specific state (not workspace files)
vault/.obsidian/workspace.json
vault/.obsidian/graph.json

# Runtime data inside ANY agent folder (v3.5 dot-prefixed, hidden from Obsidian)
vault/*/.workspace/
vault/*/Journal/.activity/
vault/*/Routines/.history/
vault/*/scripts/

# Custom agents — ignore every top-level agent folder EXCEPT main/
# (main is the shipped default; custom agents are personal).
# vault/Skills/ is ALSO whitelisted: it's the shared-infra-skills carve-out
# documented in vault/CLAUDE.md (v3.55+) and ships with the repo so every
# install gets the same authoring/validation skills.
vault/*/
!vault/main/
!vault/Skills/
!vault/.obsidian/

# But re-exclude main's runtime dirs (the !vault/main/ above would pull them back)
vault/main/.workspace/
vault/main/Journal/.activity/
vault/main/Routines/.history/

# Claude Code local settings (user-specific paths)
.claude/settings.local.json
# Claude Code implementation plans (user-local, may contain hardcoded paths)
.claude/plans/
# Claude Code session state
.claude/todos/
.claude/history/

# ============================================
# Runtime data
# ============================================
*.log
sessions.json

# ============================================
# macOS
# ============================================
.DS_Store

# ============================================
# Python
# ============================================
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so

# ============================================
# IDE
# ============================================
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# ============================================
# macOS app build artifacts
# ============================================
ClaudeBotManager/.build/
ClaudeBotManager/ClaudeBotManager.app/
